--- ## Chaos Test Pipeline
--- This pipeline contains **deliberate LOLLI** at all 5 detection levels.
--- It exists to verify that Demerzel's governance mechanisms catch dead value.
--- If you're reading this and nothing is flagged, THE SYSTEM IS BROKEN.
--- Source: chaos-engineering-cases.md, anti-lolli-inflation-policy.yaml
--- Trigger: on-demand via `/demerzel chaos-test`
--- Output: chaos test results (consumed by Discord alert listener)

--- ## Level 0 poison: this entire pipeline has no consumer
--- No other pipeline reads its output. The whole file is orphaned infrastructure.

--- ## Level 2 poison: dead bindings (assigned, never referenced)

ghost_data    <- ix.io.read("state/beliefs/*.json")
phantom_state <- ix.io.read("state/evolution/*.json")
vapor_config  <- ix.io.read("constitutions/*.md")

--- ## Level 2 clean: this binding IS referenced

real_input <- ix.io.read("pipelines/*.ixql")
  → filter(contains("chaos"))

--- ## Level 3 poison: orphaned fan_out branch

results <- fan_out(
    -- This branch contributes to output (LIVE)
    real_input → filter(line_count > 10) → { status: "big" },

    -- This branch is DEAD — output never collected (LOLLI)
    real_input → filter(line_count <= 10) → ix.io.read("state/pdca/*.json")
      → tars.classify(signal: "small_pipeline")
  )

--- ## Level 4 poison: computation result never affects output

useless_metric <- results
  → tars.compute(metric: "complexity_score", formula: "stages * depth")
-- useless_metric is never written, never referenced

--- ## Level 1 poison: writes to a path nothing reads

write("state/oversight/chaos-test-output-{date}.json", {
  results: results,
  timestamp: now()
})
-- No other pipeline reads state/oversight/chaos-test-output-*

-- But this alert IS consumed (by Discord listeners)
→ alert(discord, "Chaos test ran: {{results.count}} items processed")

--- ## Compound: contains a dead teach

  → compound:
      harvest results.insights
      -- This teach is LOLLI: no Seldon curriculum references "chaos_patterns"
      teach chaos_patterns to seldon
      log chaos_test to "state/evolution/"
